Privacy Policy — BudgetBlock
Last updated: April 2026
Summary: BudgetBlock does not collect, transmit, or share any personal data. Everything stays on your device.
What BudgetBlock does
BudgetBlock is a Chrome extension that lets you set daily time budgets for distracting websites. When your budget runs out, the site is blocked until midnight. It is distributed internally to Ellen MacArthur Foundation staff.
Data we collect
BudgetBlock stores the following data locally on your device only, using Chrome's built-in storage APIs: the list of websites you choose to block, the time budget and block style you set for each site, and how much of your daily budget you have used per site (reset at midnight). This data never leaves your browser. It is not sent to any server, third party, or to Ellen MacArthur Foundation systems.
Data we do not collect
We do not collect your browsing history, identity or account information, diagnostic or usage analytics, or any data from websites you visit.
Permissions explained
Storage — saves your blocked sites list and daily usage locally. Tabs — detects which site you are viewing so time can be tracked against your budget. Alarms — refreshes the toolbar countdown every minute and resets usage at midnight. Host permissions — allows the extension to run on any page to check whether it is on your blocked list.
Third parties
BudgetBlock does not use any third-party services, analytics platforms, or external APIs. No data is shared with any third party under any circumstances.
Data retention and deletion
Daily usage resets automatically at midnight. Your site list persists until you remove it manually or uninstall the extension. Uninstalling removes all locally stored data.
Remote code
BudgetBlock does not load or execute any remote code. All code runs from files bundled within the extension package.
Contact
Maintained by the IT team at Ellen MacArthur Foundation. Questions can be directed to the internal IT helpdesk.
